        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> findPath()
        The method finds the shortest path between a start and end coordinate in a graph using BFS traversal.
        Returns:
        a List of Strings representing the shortest path from the start coordinate to the end coordinate in a graph. If there is no path from the start to the end coordinate, it returns null.
